neutral.name: Neutral Space
neutral.desc: This space can be freely traversed and have no additional effects.

altar.name: Altar
altar.desc: A player on this space is allowed to make one wish. At the end of the turn, all players who made wishes have their wishes granted and then are returned to Start. Multiple players on this space do not engage in combat.

start.name: Start Square
start.desc: All new players start on this square. Players sharing this space do not fight, and any player on this space does not lose HP for any reason. A player who ends his turn on Start is cured of any status ailments.

gap.name: Empty Gap
gap.desc: These spaces are ordinarily impassible to players. If a player is forced onto a gap, they immediately return to Start and loses 5 HP. A player who is adjacent to a gap can choose to leap into the gap.

shop.name: Shop
shop.desc: A player who lands on this space receives a random item, if there is room in the player's inventory.

lava.name: Lava Space
lava.desc: Any player who passes this space and has more than 1 HP has their HP instantly decreased to 1. Tokens will try to avoid Lava Spaces if possible.

hell.name: Hell Tile
hell.visual: half-sized blue space with green continent
hell.desc: Any player who passes this space is afflicted with the Black Butter status effect. While there is no one on this space, it may randomly emit Hostile Cows.

mtn.name: Really Wide Mountain
mtn.visual: dark gray space with brown mountains
mtn.desc: In order to move from this space to a space without "Mountain" in the name, a player must jump off the mountain, losing 5 HP in the process.

saus.name: Sausage Space
saus.visual: faded gray space with brown sausage
saus.desc: A player who lands on this space gets a sausage. This is not an item; it's a form of currency.

hosp.name: Angry Hospital Space
hosp.desc: Whenever a player passes this space, an Angry Nurse will appear on it. This Angry Nurse will always pursue the player who passed the space.

pt.name: P/T Space
pt.desc: This space can't decide if it's a Pizza Hut or a Taco Bell. If it's a Pizza Hut and a player lands on it, they get a pizza-themed item. If it's a Taco Bell, they get a taco-themed item instead. There's a 1% chance when a player lands on it, that this space will currently be a Homicidal Maniac Space and will give them an item with a severe negative effect.

black.name: Black Hole
black.desc: Time passes slower near a black hole. Any player who ends their turn on this space is held back a turn. That means that that player considers the board to be as it was a turn ago. Wishes and other effects that the affected player uses to affect the board only affect it in the present day. This affliction is cured if the player passes or lands on Start. These spaces have no effect on non-player tokens.

ann1.name: Annoying Trap #1
ann1.desc: A player who passes this space loses 1 HP, unless they already have only 1 HP left. This space then transforms into another random "Annoying Trap" space.

ann2.name: Annoying Trap #2
ann2.desc: A player who passes this space loses a random item. This space then transforms into another random "Annoying Trap" space.

ann3.name: Annoying Trap #3
ann3.desc: A player who passes this space must stop here for this turn. This space then transforms into another random "Annoying Trap" space.

ann4.name: Annoying Trap #4
ann4.desc: A player who passes this space is afflicted with the Sliced Bread status effect. This space then transforms into another random "Annoying Trap" space.

loaded.name: Loaded Spring Space
loaded.visual: green space with three black right-arrows
loaded.desc: A player on this space gains 1 MOV per real-life day that they spend on this space. At the end of the turn that a player moves off this space, their MOV reverts to whatever it was before they stepped on it.

tele.name: Teleport Space
tele.visual: teal space with black unfilled diamond
tele.desc: A player or token who passes this space is teleported to a random location. This space will never teleport a player to another Teleport Space, a space containing a player or token, a hazardous space, the Altar, or a space with a gold coin.

click.name: Click-the-Clown Space
click.visual: dark yellow space with white mouse cursor
click.desc: Every time a player lands on this space, the Clown Counter increases by 1. If the Clown Counter ever hits six, a boss fight against the Final Clown begins.

blobby.name: Mr. Blobby
blobby.visual: massive space depicted inflatable assaulted by car
blobby.desc: Mr. Blobby can see the future. Whenever a player passes his space, he looks into that player's future to see if they're going to make a really silly wish. If they are, he inflicts damage to them in proportion to the inanity of the wish. Mr. Blobby will never inflict lethal damage.

code.name: The Code
code.desc: WUAS' source code is stored here. Unfortunately, it's encrypted, so you can't read it or change it. If there is ever not a gold coin on this space, the space will transform into something harmful.

calzone.name: Calzone
calzone.desc: You just have to special, don't you? In that case, I'm not telling you what this item does. Single use.

bitpizza.name: Bitwise Pizza
bitpizza.desc: Single use. Preserve your energy by becoming bitwise. +2 MOV for the current turn.

varypizza.name: Variety Pizza
varypizza.desc: Single use. Gain 1 ATK, 1 DEF, and 1 MOV for the current turn. +1 HP when used.

pinepizza.name: Pineapple Pizza
pinepizza.desc: Are you actually going to eat that? Single use. Permanent +1 ATK, but when you use this item, you're left with Memory of Pineapple Pizza in your inventory.

pepppizza.name: Pepperoni Pizza
pepppizza.desc: Single use. Gain 3 ATK for the current turn. Simple and straightforward.

mempinepizza.name: Memory of Pineapple Pizza
mempinepizza.desc: You actually ate it?! This item cannot be dropped voluntarily. Any post you make which does not contain the phrase "I can't believe I actually ate that" will be considered null and void, and actions in that post will be ignored.

pizzagun.name: Pizza Gun
pizzagun.desc: Once per turn, you may shoot pizza sauce at a player on an adjacent space or the same space as you. That player will be mildly annoyed and will not be able to attack you for the current turn.

emap.name: Empty Board Map
emap.desc: This isn't very useful. It was recently destroyed by a cataclysm, so now it's just an empty map.

meteor.name: Meteor
meteor.desc: Select an item anywhere on the board or in any player's inventory and throw this meteor at it. That item transforms into a useless variant of itself. This Meteor is then moved to the space the item was on or into the target player's inventory. If there's no room, it is dropped at the target player's feet.

merctailor.name: Mercerenies the Tailor
merctailor.desc: As long as this item is in your inventory, it will happily make you custom-made suits. Once per turn, you can employ your private tailor to build you an article of clothing that will boost your stats by a small amount. If this item is ever dropped, Mercerenies gets to make his wish come true.

beemovie.name: Bee Movie Space
beemovie.desc: This space is an item, for some reason. Every time you use it, a random word from the Bee Movie will be printed in the Happenings section of the update. If you want to use this item more than once on a given turn, each subsequent activation costs 1 HP.

striped.name: Striped Suit of Racing
striped.desc: +2 MOV as long as you're holding this. But this suit will burn up if you ever pass a Lava Space.

cutecat.name: Cute Cat
cutecat.desc: A cute cat with a dark side. If you pass a non-player token while holding this cat, it will automatically leap out of your hands and instantly kill the token. The cat disappears after doing this.

bcalzone.name: Blue Calzone
bcalzone.desc: I'm still not telling you what this does. Single use.

bmerc.name: Blue Mercerenies
bmerc.desc: A very sad Mercerenies. He's so sad that he's not going to make you any more clothes. You can make him less sad by collecting two gold coins. If you drop this item, then it turns into Red Mercerenies, an angry token.

bbmovie.name: Blue Bee Movie Space
bbmovie.desc: Wouldn't the Bee Movie be so much better if it was in blue? When you use this item, the next update will contain a picture from the Bee Movie but in blue. Single use.

bracing.name: Blue Racing Suit
bracing.desc: +4 MOV as long as you hold this item, but it burns up if you are ever attacked by a player or a token.

bbitwise.name: Blue Bitwise Pizza
bbitwise.desc: Single use. Preserve your energy by becoming blue and bitwise. +2 MOV for the current turn, and any players you pass have their items turned blue for the current turn.

magbag.name: Magic Bag
magbag.desc: Select an adjacent or diagonal player. That player is inflicted with a random status effect. You may use this item up to once per turn.

norgun.name: Norwegian Gun
norgun.desc: +3 ATK as long as you hold this item, but every sentence you make must contain the word "Norway" or "Norwegian". If you break this rule, this item disintigrates.

rocket.name: Rocketship
rocket.desc: Single use. Select a cardinal direction to launch yourself in. You will land on the next non-gap space in that direction.

wings.name: Magic Wings
wings.desc: Spaces and items with "Gravity" in the name do not affect you while you hold this item. You may also walk freely over gaps with no penalty. If you end the turn on a gap, you will still fall through, though.

porter.name: Teleporter
porter.desc: Single use. Teleports the player to another board, one with more gold coins.

blueppizza.name: Blue Pepperoni Pizza
blueppizza.desc: Single use. Gain 4 ATK for the current turn. Simple, straightforward, and blue.

bluevpizza.name: Blue Variety Pizza
bluevpizza.desc: Single use. Gain 1 ATK, 1 DEF, and 1 MOV for the current turn. +1 HP when used. When you use this item, you get a regular Variety Pizza in its place.

bluepgun.name: Blue Pizza Gun
bluepgun.desc: Once per turn, you may shoot pizza sauce at a player on an adjacent space or the same space as you. That player will be mildly annoyed and will not be able to attack you for the current turn. They will also be afflicted with Bluest Blue.

bluembag.name: Blue Magic Bag
bluembag.desc: Single use. Select any player. That player is inflicted with a random status effect.

effects.name: Black Butter
effects.desc: This is just part of the hazing ritual if you're new in Hell. MOV is halved (rounded down) as long as you have this effect, but Lava Spaces will not reduce your HP below 3.

effects.name: Sliced Bread
effects.desc: You are soft like a slice of bread. Players and tokens who attack you will deal double damage.

effects.name: Bluest Blue
effects.desc: You may choose to ignore the effects of spaces, items, and tokens which have the name "Blue" in them.

effects.name: Potatoes
effects.desc: You are now a potato. If at any point you pick up or are carrying an item with "potato" in the name, you will become disgusted with the humans' treatment of your kind and lose your sanity. Your movements on the subsequent turn will be completely random, regardless of whether or not you post.

item.name: Item
item.desc: Icon used to represent items on the map.

goldcoin.name: Gold Coin
goldcoin.desc: Can be picked up by a player. Always protected from wishes.

pinepiece.name: Piece of Pineapple
pinepiece.desc: When a player passes this token, it disappears and the player gains 10 points. If a Piece of Pineapple ever hits 0 HP, it will transform into a random, very angry token that will pursue whoever dealt the damage.

hostilecow.name: Hostile Cow
hostilecow.desc: Pursues nearby players and attacks them. Hostile Cows are unaffected by Lava Spaces and will not try to avoid them. There can only be three of these tokens on the board at a time.

sailorblue.name: Sailor Blue
sailorblue.desc: He's like Sailor Moon, but instead of drawing his power from the moon, he draws it out of the blue. Moves randomly, and every time he passes a player, he attacks them and then all of that player's items are turned blue. Every turn, he spontaneously becomes more powerful as one of his stats randomly increases.

father.name: Father
father.desc: Moves randomly. Any player who passes him must tell him a dad joke that he hasn't heard before, or they will be forced to stop on the space and be lectured, dropping their MOV to 0 for the next turn.

mother.name: Mother
mother.desc: Whenever a player passes her, she gives them a Cookie. If they already have a Cookie, she scolds them for being greedy, forcing that player to stop on the current space.

steve.name: Steve the Girlfriend
steve.desc: Moves toward the nearest player. Immediately dates and then dumps any player she meets. Any player who passes her immediately returns to Start after being dumped. If any player ever says the name "Michelle" in their post, she will immediately jump to that player's space and attack them for not using her nickname, dealing 6 damage.

bread.name: The Breadstick Ghost
bread.desc: Moves toward the nearest player. Attacks every player he passes unless that player can provide him with a Breadstick.

hawking.name: Stephen Hawking
hawking.desc: Moves randomly. Gives a random science-themed item to every player he passes.

babydragon.name: Baby Dragon
babydragon.desc: The dragon from several WUAS games ago had a baby. Like it's mother, this dragon will move randomly and spit fire at a random space (other than the one it's on) each turn. The targeted space is destroyed and replaced with a gap. Any players on that space are sent back to Start and take one damage.

barracks.name: Barracks
barracks.desc: Whoever brought this token into existence is its owner. This token will randomly generate aggressive tokens which will defend its owner.

troll.name: Troll
troll.desc: Does not move normally. If a player gets too close, the troll will pursue that player until death.

cactus.name: Sentient Cactus
cactus.desc: Any player who passes this cactus takes 1 damage. Any token who passes this cactus is destroyed.

redmerc.name: Red Mercerenies
redmerc.desc: Pursues players of his choice for incredibly petty reasons. Attacks any player he passes.

angrynurse.name: Angry Nurse
angrynurse.desc: Pursues the player who created her, attacking them whenever she ends up on the same space.

hcns.name: Homosexual Cyberpunk Nazis from Space
hcns.desc: A player who passes this token loses 1 HP. If the player already had only 1 HP, they are sent back to Start instead of being killed. In either case, once this token has performed its effect, it disappears.

rulings.desc: Any Altar wishes occur at the end of the turn, after all player movement is completed.
Effects which target a stat that a token lacks have no effect on the token. For example, a space that deals damage will not affect a token who has no concept of HP.

The specific nature of combat in the case of tokens which are deficient in some stats is this. All involved players or tokens who have an ATK stat will attack all involved players or tokens who have an HP stat. All such attacks happen simultaneously, and in general a token will never attack itself unless otherwise stated.

In general, an action which attempts to move into a gap is considered to be a mistake or a typo, and the player will not be allowed to move into the gap. If the movement into the gap was intentional, this should be specified in the post. This ruling does not apply if the player in question has any equipment that would enable him or her to pass the gaps without the normal penalty.

The larger the magnitude of a wish, the less likely it is to end up in the wisher's favor. That is, a simple wish is likely to go exactly as intended. A large and complicated wish may be interpreted extremely literally and the results may not be what was desired.
